reviewText:
Somewhat honest!
It may help a parent.
And the girl I hoped would win did, she had the whole package and more. Unfortunately the other girls didn't have the family backing that she did.

It is somewhat interesting just to see a little bit of how trans in Humboldt Park live, but there comes a point you feel there is none. Editing could have been better. It starts no where and takes you no where. You really don't see what happens to the lives of these girls and eventually you loose interest. There's just nothing interesting going on in Humboldt Park.
Unexpected Suprise!!!  Beautiful Ladies in Every Way!!!
Touching - real people with unreal dreams.

A poignant exploration of the personal side of this beauty pageant! Filmed and cut to capture the triumphs and tribulations, and the personal investment involved in winning the pageant. There is never a dull moment with the girls. This is one to enjoy!
